Privacy Rights Under Applicable Laws
Residents of certain U.S. states (including Colorado, Connecticut, Utah and Virginia) may also have certain rights under applicable
                privacy laws, subject to certain limitations and exceptions. These rights may include:
Right to Access/Know.
To confirm whether we are processing your personal information and
                    to access and obtain a copy of your personal information in a portable and, to the extent
                    technically feasible, readily usable format.
Right to Correct.
To correct inaccuracies in your personal information.
Right to Delete.
To delete personal information provided to or obtained about you.
Rights to Opt-Out.
To opt out of certain types of processing, including:
if applicable, to opt out of the sale your personal information.
to opt out of our use of your personal information for purposes of targeted advertising.
If applicable, to opt out of our processing of your personal information for purposes of making
                        decisions that produce legal or similarly significant effects.
Right to Appeal.
If we deny your request, you may be able to appeal our decision by contacting
                    us at
privacy@conair.com
.
